The paper deals with ranking search results and ads based on user click models, which is a core problem in information retrieval (IR) and data structures (DS). The proposed ranking function also considers optimal utility and has the same time complexity as sorting, which suggests a machine learning (LG) component. The paper also discusses a pricing mechanism for ad auctions, which falls under game theory (GT) and computational complexity (CC).
